” became evidence at Nuremberg. Grossman’s powerful anti†‘totalitarian works liken the Nazis’ crimes against humanity with those of Stalin. His compassionate prose has the everlasting quality of great art. Because Grossman’s major works appeared after much delay we are only now able to examine them properly. Alexandra Popoff’s authoritative biography illuminates Grossman’s life and legacy.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Jun 2021) 0aAuthors, Russiany20th centuryvBiography. 0aDissenterszSoviet UnionvBiography. 0aJewish authorszSoviet UnionvBiography. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Literary.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishz978311061076508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural and Area Stud. 2019 Englishz978311061036908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural and Area Studies 2019z9783110606348oZDB-23-DKU08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311065488240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300245301423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780300245301.jpg  a978-3-11-061036-9  EBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural and Area Stud. 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-061076-5  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-065488-2  Yale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2019b2019  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2019  aZDB-23-DKUb2019